 {"id": ["mesh:D013739"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "Testosterone", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9957085847854614, "span": {"begin": 331, "end": 343}}, {"id": ["mesh:D003687"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "DHEA", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9988065958023071, "span": {"begin": 369, "end": 373}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "human theca cells", "obj": "cell_type", "prob": 0.6985216736793518, "span": {"begin": 377, "end": 394}}, {"id": ["NCBITaxon:9606"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "human", "obj": "species", "prob": 0.9978607296943665, "span": {"begin": 377, "end": 382}}, {"id": ["mesh:D003687"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "DHEA", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9993832111358643, "span": {"begin": 449, "end": 453}}, {"id": ["mesh:D013739"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "testosterone", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9940472841262817, "span": {"begin": 472, "end": 484}}, {"id": ["mesh:D003687"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "DHEA", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9975773692131042, "span": {"begin": 500, "end": 504}}, {"id": ["mesh:D013739"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "testosterone", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9458855986595154, "span": {"begin": 534, "end": 546}}], "text": "It is well established that DHEA is a precursor for testosterone (Fl&uuml;ck, 2017; Naamneh Elzenaty, 2022).&nbsp;  Testosterone is produced in human Leydig cells from DHEA via androstenedione or androstenediol by the enzymes 3-beta-hydroxysteroid dehydrogenase (3-beta-HSD) and 17-beta-hydroxysteroid dehydrogenase (17-beta-HSD). Testosterone is also synthesized from DHEA in human theca cells (Fl&uuml;ck, 2017; Naamneh Elzenaty, 2022).&nbsp;  As DHEA is a precursor of testosterone, any effect on DHEA levels is expected to impact testosterone as well.", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 15:16:50 +0000 2026"}